event.title: 1821, there were two counties that formed

data.event: In 1821, there were two counties that formed Florida: Escambia to the west and St. Johns to the east.

event.title: 1824, the area to the south of St. Johns County became

data.event: In 1824, the area to the south of St. Johns County became Mosquito County, and Enterprise was named the county seat.
Mosquito County was renamed Orange County in 1845 when Florida became a state.
